-- Emirates Airline Needs 60,000 Extra Staff in 10 Years, National Reports
-- Zainab Fattah
-- 2010-07-11T05:33:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/emirates-airline-needs-60-000-extra-staff-in-10-years-national-reports.html

          
          
             Emirates, Dubai’s state-owned
airline, will need to hire more than 60,000 new employees in the
next 10 years,  The National  reported, citing the company’s vice
president of recruitment, Rick Helliwell.  
 The airline will need an additional 2,500 pilots and 20,000
cabin crew over the period, newspaper reported.  
